@BiGulpsHuuh @Tanthos1 @dogecoin_rise As more services take dogecoin as a form of payment, the increase in doge supply will lead to an increase in the number of services/goods that can be bought. No cap on doge is a good thing when people stop seeing it as an investment and instead focus on it as a currency.

#dogecoin being uncapped doesn't really matter as it protects against lost wallets and hardware failure. It has built-in resiliency. It also allows economic activity to increase as more doge enters circulation.

🧵Money Theory Applied to #Dogecoin:
if doge supply increases, economic activity will rise, too, and vice versa as represented by MV = PQ. M (doge supply), V (average annual doge spent), P (price of goods/services), and Q (number of goods and services.) https://t.co/ukgVeQPn5Q
